<topic template="Default" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Stepping Through Code</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Stepping Through Code</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Assuming that the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Debugger</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> was invoked as a result of a resumable exception (such as via #</text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">halt</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">) you can make use of the stepping commands to continue execution. The commands available in the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> menu and are </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Step Into</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Step Over</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Step Out</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Run to Cursor</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Run</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, and </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Animate</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. .</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug/Step Into</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">command provides the finest granularity of movement, and steps into the next method or block activation (i.e. into the next message send). If the next message is an indivisible primitive operation (such as </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">SmallInteger</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> addition) then the command steps over this to the next expression. The </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Step Into</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command is disabled if the top stack frame is not selected.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug/Step Over</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">command steps to the next expression (i.e. the next message send, assignment, or return) in the currently selected stack frame.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug/Step Out </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">command continues execution until the currently selected stack frame has returned to its sender.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug/Run to Cursor</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command continues execution until it reaches the expression whose start point is nearest the caret position in the </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Source</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane. If execution never reaches that expression, then execution continues as if a </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Go</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command had been issued</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug/Run</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command closes the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Debugger</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and resumes execution of the process from where it left off.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug/Animate</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> allows you to toggle automatic single-stepping. If on, then the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Debugger</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> steps through the process and it updates the various panes to show the current execution state as it goes. The speed at which the animation proceeds can be configured by the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Debugger</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> system option, </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">animatePause</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">,</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> which determines the time in milliseconds between steps</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When you have finished debugging a process, you can explicitly terminate the process by closing the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Debugger</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or with the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Debug/Terminate</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> command.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Notes"><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">You can learn a lot about Dolphin by stepping though base system code in the Debugger, but be careful when placing </text><text styleclass="Notes" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">#halt</text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true"> messages in base system methods when they might be used by the debugger itself. Doing so will probably cause a recursive walkback and the of then crash the system. Save your image </text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">before </text><text styleclass="Notes" translate="true">doing anything you suspect might be compromising.</text></para>
  </body>
